00:04:25.164 --> 00:04:27.096
What does it represent?

00:04:27.096 --> 00:04:28.446
We've already thought about these like

00:04:28.446 --> 00:04:30.864
these really small rectangles.

00:04:30.864 --> 00:04:34.180
And we're taking the
sum of the limit of an

00:04:34.180 --> 00:04:37.413
infinite number of these
infinitely thin rectangles.

00:04:37.413 --> 00:04:39.099
But when we're thinking
about Riemann sums,

00:04:39.099 --> 00:04:41.648
we're thinking about okay
we have some change in x,

00:04:41.648 --> 00:04:44.829
and then you multiply it
times essentially the height,

00:04:44.829 --> 00:04:45.687
which is going to be the value

00:04:45.687 --> 00:04:47.896
of the function at that point.

00:04:47.896 --> 00:04:51.698
Well over here, you could
have the same change in x.

00:04:51.698 --> 00:04:53.713
You can have the exact same change in x.

00:04:53.713 --> 00:04:56.198
And what is the height right over here?

00:04:56.198 --> 00:04:58.299
Well, that's going to be this
exact height right over here.

00:04:58.299 --> 00:05:00.015
You saw that when we constructed it.

00:05:00.015 --> 00:05:03.298
This is going to be the
