00:05:35.630 --> 00:05:37.129
And so this area right over here,

00:05:37.129 --> 00:05:38.797
and I'm obviously not
doing a rigorous proof,

00:05:38.797 --> 00:05:40.298
I'm giving you the intuition for it,

00:05:40.298 --> 00:05:44.847
is the exact same thing as
this area right over here.

00:05:44.847 --> 00:05:46.447
So the area under this curve,

00:05:46.447 --> 00:05:50.598
the definite integral from a
to b of f of x plus g of x, dx,

00:05:50.598 --> 00:05:55.598
is just going to be the sum of
these two definite integrals.

00:05:57.848 --> 00:05:59.901
And you might say, "Oh this is obvious".

00:05:59.901 --> 00:06:01.297
Or maybe it's not so obvious.

